        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 10:04PM CDT by NWS Springfield MO</headline>
        <description>At 1004 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Columbus, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Columbus, Galena, Lowell, Scammon, West Mineral, Roseland, Neutral,
Riverton, Carona, Skidmore, Hallowell, Sherwin, Stippville, and
Crestline.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
